Ages,<span class="ff10"> p. 28.</span></span></div><div class="t m0 x4c h36 y5bb ff10 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws38">This week, as we continue to study the book of Amos, we will see </div><div class="t m0 x4a h36 y5bc ff10 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws49">even more of the ways in which the Lord pled with His people to put </div><div class="t m0 x4a h36 y5bd ff10 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 wsa7">away their sins and return unto Him, the only true Source of life. In </div><div class="t m0 x4a h36 y5be ff10 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6f">the end, we all have only one of two choices: life or death. There is </div><div class="t m0 x4a h36 y5bf ff10 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 wsc2">no middle ground. Amos shows us a little more about the stark differ<span class="ws4">-</span></div><div class="t m0 x4a h36 y5c0 ff10 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5">ences between these choices.</div><div class="t m0 x53 h36 y5c1 fff fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5">*Study this week’s lesson to prepare for Sabbath, May 4.</div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
